article.description: — Jamaine Mann came off the bench to score 18 points to carry Gardner-Webb to an 84-57 win over UNC-Asheville on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Mann lifts Gardner-Webb past UNC Asheville 84-57
article.linkText: Mann lifts Gardner-Webb past UNC Asheville 84-57
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- — Jamaine Mann came off the bench to score 18 points to carry Gardner-Webb to an 84-57 win over UNC-Asheville on Wednesday night. D’Maurian Williams had 16 points for Gardner-Webb (4-9, 3-5 Big South Conference). Jacob Falko added 11 points and seven rebounds. Jordan Sears had 10 points. Ludovic Dufeal tied a career high with six blocks plus six points and seven rebounds. Gardner-Webb scored 47 points in the first half, a season best for the team. DeVon Baker had 20 points for the Bulldogs (8-7, 7-3), whose four-game winning streak was broken. UNC-Asheville defeated Gardner-Webb 79-75 on Tuesday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
